message.content:
There are several ways to view your browsing history on Google Chrome:

Method 1:
1. Open your Google Chrome browser.
2. Press Ctrl + H (Windows) or Cmd + Y (Mac) keys simultaneously.
3. A new tab will open showing you the complete browsing history organized by date and time.

Method 2:
1. Open your Google Chrome browser.
2. Click on the 'three-dot menu' icon in the top right corner of the browser window.
3. Hover over 'History', and a submenu will appear with recently visited sites and an option for viewing more extensive browsing history called 'History.' Click on it, and this will display your full browsing history in a new tab.

In both methods, you can use the search bar at the top of the History page to find specific websites or pages visited in your past browsing sessions quickly.
